<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/2818106-cece"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2818106-cece">Cece</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It is not. This book is the true account of a storm that developed quickly in late September 1938. It was expected to hit Florida but instead stayed o<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It is not. This book is the true account of a storm that developed quickly in late September 1938. It was expected to hit Florida but instead stayed off the East Coast as it rapidly traveled northerly and became extra-tropical. It eventually slammed into New England with no advance warning; no one in its path had any idea that what they were experiencing was a fierce hurricane. Many lives were lost and the property damage was catastrophic. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
