              <span id="reviewTextContainer448615896" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4482240566726782557">Great book. Of particular interest to someone living in New England now, after Hurricane Sandy, I believe. Tremendous loss of life and property with the Great Hurricane of 1938, making us realize Hurricane Sandy, while tragic and did so much damage, was not unusual in this area after all. Definitely recommend the book. The author wrote based on human stories of those that survived, and those that did not.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


